  "elapsed_s": 12.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And there, and not far from-- from the park, there were no [INAUDIBLE] coming out with [INAUDIBLE] hand, you see.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And she just simply emptied out her pockets to the-- to-- to the kids.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "She was so-- so really loving heart, and you see, to watch it is humane, real humane.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were how are you going to get home?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "How are you going to buy-- buy streetcar to get home? 'Oh, you're going to carry me home.' OK.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] Simple as that, she has this-- this characteristic that I-- I didn't find out half for it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Only when I read her diary then.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was who she-- who she really was.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Did she write you any poems?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, no.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And only-- only after the war, when here in-- in Toronto through Rabbi [?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Sagem. ?] Have you ever heard of him?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He's a Hungarian-- Hungarian rabbi.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he visited Miss Szenes and-- and Julie there several-- several times.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then when-- when he came back, I already-- I already had the book to English of her diary.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Rabbi [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Sagem ?] came me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He gave me some-- some of the smaller, smaller, smaller books what was written in-- in-- in Israel, and-- and some in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But never a full story about-- about her.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I-- I-- I really couldn't find-- find out the whole thing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But then when I was then introduced to Rabbi [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Sagem, ?] he took that news.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "If they'd ever heard about me, [INAUDIBLE] or George.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the only thing that they could remember, because there the-- the postal service was-- was really bad.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they were never allowed to-- to-- to correspond.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And anyway, but there were what you call runners between Cairo and-- Cairo Palestine, so.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
